# Core Clauses
[[NEC3]] contracts have a set of nine [[Core Clauses]]. These are the same in every form, and cover the [[Contract]] basics.

*As per Pinsent Mason's List - [Link](https://www.pinsentmasons.com/out-law/guides/standard-form-contracts-nec)

-   1 - general - includes defined terms, interpretation, communications, ambiguities;
-   2 ‚Äì contractor's main responsibilities ‚Äì provision of works, design, people, subcontracting;
-   3 ‚Äì time ‚Äì starting, completion dates, key dates, programme, access, takeover, acceleration;
-   4 ‚Äì testing and defects ‚Äì tests and inspections, notifying defects, correcting defects, accepting defects, uncorrected defects;
-   5 ‚Äì payment ‚Äì assessing amounts due, payment provisions, pain share/gain share where appropriate;
-   6 ‚Äì [[Compensation Event (CE)]]s ‚Äì events which will give rise to time and money and procedures for dealing with these;
-   7 ‚Äì title ‚Äì for example, to plant and materials;
-   8 ‚Äì [[Risk]] and insurance ‚Äì contractor and employer risks, insurance requirements;
-   9 ‚Äì termination ‚Äì grounds, procedures and payments on/for termination.












